message.content:
cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.ET, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a highly likely category as the paper deals with temporal logics and their formalization.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper proposes a new notation for specifying patterns of behaviors.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the practical usefulness of the proposed notation and its application in checking consistency of timing diagram requirements and automatic synthesis of property monitors and controllers.
- cs.ET (Embedded Systems) is relevant as the paper deals with timing diagram requirements over hardware and embedded controllers.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper gives examples of a minepump controller and a bus arbiter to illustrate the proposed tools.
